description:
This submission provides R-code and data files for our peer reviewed work (currently in preprint).&nbsp; 

 The first set of R-notebooks, 1, 2, 3, relate to the effects of diethyl maleate (DEM) and neonicotinoid imidacloprid and thiacloprid on springtail reproduction.&nbsp; 

A separate set of notebooks, numbered 4 and 5, contain the R-code for analyzing the effects of neonicotinoid and DEM exposure on springtail gene expression (qPCR). The gene expression data is output directly generated by the qPCR machine accompanying software, therefore, it contains many NaNs or non-sensible rows. 

 The submission consists of:&nbsp; 

 - Rmd; R notebooks as described above.&nbsp; 

 - .csv; count data&nbsp; of springtail juveniles and adults or gene expression values.&nbsp; 

 This research was financed by the Dutch Research Council (NWO) domain Applied and Engineering Sciences (TTW) (Project number 15494).

